summary: Culture has always played a vital role to my life and it was inevitable to pursue a different career path. I studied archeology and history of art and I have also graduated from a drama school in Greece. The last years my focus is on the museum sector. I was an intern at the National Gallery of Greece where I was responsible for the touring guides, I have volunteered for several cultural projects and I have worked as an assistant curator at Frissiras contemporary museum in Greece. There I did touring guides and managed the organizational aspect of the museum. I have also worked as a researcher of oral history at the NGO Istorima where I was part of the team responsible for the  interviews and transcriptions. I am currently doing my master in Museums and Collections in Leiden University.
